      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for nmstate.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Nmstate is a library with an accompanying command line tool that manages host\nnetworking settings in a declarative manner.\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* Cannot configure IP on an ovs interface which has the same name with ovs bridge (BZ#1979220)\n\n* libnmstate expects VF to be named differently to its actual name. (BZ#1979515)\n\n* [OVS] Adding route rules to interface fails with error (BZ#1979943)\n\n* Verification fails with next hop address 0.0.0.0 (BZ#1986285)\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
